entries.title_d: An  Imperial Transport bearing weapons for the Imperial Research Station on Endor has been badly damaged in an escape from rebel pilots.  Track down the freighter with the provided homing waypoint and get them back underway to the station.
entries.title: Naboo System: Deliverance
entries.thanks_3: Just a bit longer then we will make the jump.
entries.thanks_2: Not so viscious now that there is a ship with guns firing back.
entries.taunt_3: Your friend there will be no help to you.
entries.taunt_2: I knew we would find you nearby.
entries.taunt_1: This time there will be no escape.
entries.split_quest_alert: \#pcontrast3 Endor Station: < \#pcontrast1 The transport is away.  Hyperspace to the Endor System, navpoint Area D-435 to make the rendezvous here and complete the mission. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.rescue_phase_2: Emergency startup is complete, lets get out of here Captain.
entries.rescue_phase_1: Interlocks engaged, begining engine jumpstart sequence now.
entries.rescue_abandoned: This is why the empire is a worse place for working with mercenaries.
entries.recovery_success: \#pcontrast3 Endor Station: < \#pcontrast1 The transport has informed us they made the jump from the Naboo System. Their destination point is near the Area D-435 hyperspace point in the Endor System.  Meet them there and finish bringing them into the station. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.quest_location_d: The transport dropped out of Hyperspace early after an emergency jump to escape from the Rebel attack craft.  Location will be updated when you are in range of their distress signal.
entries.quest_escort_d: Escort the Transport safely to their jump point in the Naboo system and Rendezvous with them in Endor to complete the mission.
entries.quest_dock_d: Target the transport and use the /dock command to initiate the repair procedure.
entries.failed_destroy: \#pcontrast3 Endor Staion: < \#pcontrast1 Oh, this is most terrible. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.attack_stopped: \#pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < \#pcontrast1 Hostile actions have ceased. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.attack_notify: \#pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < \#pcontrast1 Hostile craft detected on attack vector. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_2: \#pcontrast3 Nav Computer: < \#pcontrast1 Distress signal located.  Target location locked in. \#pcontrast3 >
entries.arrival_phase_1: \#pcontrast3 Tactical Computer: < \#pcontrast1 Searching for the transports distress beacon... stand by.
entries.abort: I am not hanging around here with no escort.
